documentation.text:
@title Sensor
 @dev A smart contract for registering and managing sensors for tracking parcels

@dev Attach the sensor to a parcel
 @param _parcelId The ID of the parcel to attach the sensor to

@dev Detach the sensor from a parcel
 @param _parcelId The ID of the parcel to detach the sensor from

devdoc.details: A smart contract for registering and managing sensors for tracking parcels

attachToParcel(string).details: Attach the sensor to a parcel

params._parcelId: The ID of the parcel to attach the sensor to

detachFromParcel(string).details: Detach the sensor from a parcel

params._parcelId: The ID of the parcel to detach the sensor from

logViolation(string,string).details: Logs a violation of an SLA by the sensor attached to the parcel.      The function stores the parcel ID that the sensor is attached to,      so that when a violation occurs, it can be logged in the context of the parcel.

params._parcelId: The ID of the parcel that the sensor is attached to.
params._sla: The SLA that has been violated.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Sensor
